title: The Great Gatsby
author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
description: A classic American novel set in the Jazz Age, exploring themes of wealth, love, and the American Dream through the eyes of narrator Nick Carraway and the mysterious Jay Gatsby.

title: To Kill a Mockingbird
author: Harper Lee
description: A gripping tale of racial injustice and childhood innocence in the Depression-era South, told through the eyes of young Scout Finch.

author: George Orwell
description: A dystopian social science fiction novel exploring totalitarianism, surveillance, and the manipulation of truth in a future totalitarian society.

title: The Alchemist
author: Paulo Coelho
description: A philosophical novel about a young Andalusian shepherd's journey to Egypt after having a recurring dream of finding treasure there.

title: Advanced Physics: Concepts & Applications
author: Smith, Dr. Jane
description: Comprehensive guide to modern physics covering quantum mechanics, relativity, thermodynamics, and particle physics with practical applications.

title: Atomic Habits
author: Clear, James
description: An easy and proven way to build good habits and break bad ones, with practical strategies backed by science.

title: Digital Fortress
author: Dan Brown
description: A techno-thriller exploring the battle between privacy and national security in the digital age.

title: The Fountainhead
author: Ayn Rand
description: A novel about Howard Roark, an individualistic architect who refuses to compromise his artistic vision.

title: Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind
author: Yuval Noah Harari
description: An exploration of how Homo sapiens came to dominate the world, from the Stone Age to the modern era.

title: The Catcher in the Rye
author: J.D. Salinger
description: The story of teenage rebellion and alienation told through the eyes of Holden Caulfield over a few days in New York City.

title: Pride and Prejudice
author: Jane Austen
description: A romantic novel of manners exploring themes of marriage, morality, and misconceptions in Georgian England.

title: Sapiens
author: Yuval Noah Harari
description: A thought-provoking exploration of human history from the emergence of Homo sapiens to the present day.

title: Introduction to Machine Learning
author: Chen, Dr. Wei
description: Practical guide to machine learning algorithms, neural networks, and AI applications with Python examples.

title: The Road
author: Cormac McCarthy
description: A post-apocalyptic tale of a father and son's journey through a devastated America.

title: The Lord of the Rings
author: Tolkien, J.R.R.
description: The epic fantasy trilogy following hobbits, elves, dwarves, and men in their quest to destroy the One Ring.
